Class JULAppender

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.logging.log4j.core.filter.AbstractFilterable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Appender, Filterable, LifeCycle

    public final class JULAppender
extends AbstractAppender
    A Log4j2 appender that redirects all log events to a specified Logger. It's config name is JUL.

      • createAppender

        public static JULAppender createAppender(String name,
                         String logger,
                         String ignore,
                         Layout<? extends Serializable> layout,
                         Filter filter)
        Creates a new instance of JULAppender.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the appender
        logger - name of the Logger to which log events should be redirected
        ignore - if true, no exceptions from this appender will be propagated to the application; if false, then undefined (and is a subject to change when new features are added)
        layout - the layout to use to format the message field of LogRecord
        filter - the filter to associate with this appender
        Returns:
